Interface IUrnNamespace

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAccount, IAccountDomainResource<T>, IDevice, IDomainResource<T>, IEvent, IExtension, IFile, IGeospatialEntry, IMetadata, INamedObject<T>, INotificationEndpoint, IObject, IObjectAddress, IObjectInteraction, IObjectInteractionSession, IRelationship, IRule, ITag, ITagAssignment, ITimelineEntry, IUser
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Account, AccountNamedObject, AccountTypedNamedObject, Device, DomainResource, Event, Extension, File, GeospatialEntry, Metadata, NamedObject, NotificationEndpoint, ObjectAddress, ObjectImpl, ObjectInteraction, ObjectInteractionSession, ReferentialObject, Relationship, Tag, TagAssignment, TimelineEntry, TypedNamedObject, TypeSafeMetadata, User

    public interface IUrnNamespace
    Sole means of uniquely identifying a specific object in the SnapBundle platform. Developers must not rely on the IDomainResource.getUniqueId() value, as neither its uniqueness nor consistency is guaranteed by the SnapBundle platform.

      • getUrn

        String getUrn()
        System assigned, globally unique key used to reference a specific record. When defining a referential object, this URN maps to the IReferentialObject.getReferenceUrn() value.
        Returns:
        System-assigned UUID
        See Also:
        IReferentialObject

      • setUrn

        void setUrn(String urn)

      • getLastModifiedTimestamp

        long getLastModifiedTimestamp()
        System managed field for tracking the last time the record was updated. This field is predominately used to create a valid ETag for client-side cache management.
        Returns:
        Last modified time (based on the Unix timestamp)
